│  └────────────┘  └──────────────┘  └──────────┬───────────┘ │
│                                               │             │
│                          ┌────────────────────▼──────────┐  │
│                          │     AI Agent Service          │  │
│                          │  1. Parse intent via Gemini   │  │
│                          │  2. Extract function call     │  │
│                          │  3. Execute DB operation      │  │
│                          │  4. Return natural response   │  │
│                          └────────────────────┬──────────┘  │
└───────────────────────────────────────────────┼─────────────┘
                                                │
         ┌──────────────────────────────────────┼────────┐
         │                                      │        │
┌────────▼──────┐                  ┌────────────▼──────┐  │
│  PostgreSQL   │                  │  Google Gemini API │  │
│  (Prisma ORM) │                  │  (Function Calling)│  │
└───────────────┘                  └───────────────────┘  │
```

### Request-Response Lifecycle (AI Query)

```
1. User types: "Mark my shopping list as done"
2. POST /api/agent/query { prompt: "..." } + JWT cookie
3. auth middleware verifies token → attaches req.user
4. AgentController → AgentService.processQuery(userId, prompt)
5. AgentService calls Gemini with: systemPrompt + tools + userPrompt
6. Gemini responds: { functionCall: { name: "mark_completed", args: { titleKeyword: "shopping" } } }
7. AgentService calls NoteService.markCompleted(userId, "shopping")
8. NoteService queries DB, finds note, sets isCompleted = true
9. AgentService sends result back to Gemini for natural language synthesis
10. Gemini returns: "Done! Your shopping list note has been marked as completed."
11. Backend returns: { success: true, message: "...", note: { ... } }
12. Frontend displays the confirmation message
```

