## 3. Database Design (Updated Schema)

Your current schema is missing `title` and `tags` on the `Note` model. Here's the production upgrade:

```prisma
model User {
  id        String   @id @default(uuid())
  name      String
  email     String   @unique
  password  String
  notes     Note[]
  createdAt DateTime @default(now())
  updatedAt DateTime @updatedAt

  @@index([email])
}

model Note {
  id          String   @id @default(uuid())
  title       String                        // ← ADD THIS
  content     String   @default("")
  isCompleted Boolean  @default(false)
  tags        String[]                      // ← ADD THIS (Postgres native array)
  userId      String
  user        User     @relation(fields: [userId], references: [id], onDelete: Cascade)
  createdAt   DateTime @default(now())
  updatedAt   DateTime @updatedAt

  @@index([userId])
  @@index([title])                          // ← For search performance
}
```

> **Migration Command**: `npm run db:migrate` after updating the schema.

### Indexing Strategy

| Index | Reason |
|---|---|
| `User.email` | Fast lookups on login |
| `Note.userId` | Every query scopes to the logged-in user |
| `Note.title` | Keyword search without full table scan |
| PostgreSQL `tsvector` (Phase 3) | Full-text search across title + content |

