## 6. Security Best Practices

### JWT (Already good — strengthen further)
- ✅ HTTP-only cookies with `secure: true` in production
- ✅ 7-day expiry
- ➕ Add short-lived access tokens (15min) + refresh tokens (7 days) for production hardening

### Prompt Injection Prevention
```typescript
// In agent.controller.ts — sanitize before passing to AI
function sanitizePrompt(input: string): string {
  const maxLength = 500;
  const blacklist = /ignore previous|system prompt|you are now|act as/gi;
  return input.replace(blacklist, "[REMOVED]").slice(0, maxLength);
}
```

### Rate Limiting (Critical for Gemini Cost Control)
```typescript
// src/middleware/rateLimiter.ts
import rateLimit from "express-rate-limit";

export const agentRateLimiter = rateLimit({
  windowMs: 60 * 1000,  // 1 minute
  max: 10,              // 10 AI queries/min per IP
  message: { success: false, message: "Too many requests. Please slow down." },
  standardHeaders: true,
});
```
Install: `npm install express-rate-limit`

### CORS (Tighten from current `app.use(cors())`)
```typescript
app.use(cors({
  origin: process.env.FRONTEND_URL || "http://localhost:5173",
  credentials: true, // Required for cookie-based auth
}));
```

### Input Validation (Zod — already using it)
```typescript
// src/lib/schemas/note.schema.ts
import { z } from "zod";

export const createNoteSchema = z.object({
  title:   z.string().min(1).max(200),
  content: z.string().max(10000).optional().default(""),
  tags:    z.array(z.string().max(50)).max(10).optional().default([]),
});

export const agentQuerySchema = z.object({
  prompt: z.string().min(1).max(500),
});
```

